Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic. diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together. recommended resolution - A reccomendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold. responses\: success - sublist is contained in container. 229a58cf-2cf3-4782-b9d0-6916d1bd3e42.19a9b05d-5592-48b8-ba49-60ff6c072c5b.description=
Pings the requested machine from a remote host

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the host to ping from.
username - The username to use to authenticate to host.
password - The password to use to authenticate to host.
target - The target server to ping.
packets - The number of packets to send to target.
packetSize - The size of packets to send to target.

Responses\:
passed - a successful connection was made
failure - target did not respond to ping.
Connection Error - Unable to connect to host.
Unknown Target - could not resolve target to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
output - raw output of the results
address - actual IP address pinged
% Packet Loss - The percentage of packets that ping replies were received for.
average latency - The average ping response time in milliseconds.
max latency - The maximum response time of all the pings (in milliseconds).
min latency - the minimum number of milliseconds it took to receive a ping response.

Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 229a58cf-2cf3-4782-b9d0-6916d1bd3e42.45119b71-33ad-4cc4-adf9-a30a8d9a34df.prompt=Here is your diagnostic for ${host} 229a58cf-2cf3-4782-b9d0-6916d1bd3e42.4d419a27-925a-43ff-9a52-86cd3a097566.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Performing trace route diagnostic. 229a58cf-2cf3-4782-b9d0-6916d1bd3e42.description=
Checks to see whether or not a connection exists, and if it exists checks to see if it is adequately reliable. Diagnoses what is wrong with the connection.

Inputs\:
host - the host to ping from.
target - the host to ping
lossThreshold - What percentage of packet loss you consider to be acceptable for this connection.
latencyThreshold - How long (in milliseconds) you consider to be an acceptable latency for this connection.
diagnostic so far - The result of previous diagnosis, used for chaining.
maxhops - How many hops traceroute diagnostic will descend.
notifyMethod - How to report the diagnostic.
username - username for host.
password - password for host.

Responses\:
success - no problems found.
diagnosed - problems found.
failure - something went wrong.

Results\:
average latency - The average ping response time in milliseconds.
% Packet Loss - The percentage of packets that ping replies were received for.

Recommended Thresholds\:

Connection Type		Loss Threshold (%)	Latency Threshold (ms)
DSL modem			2		200
Cable modem		2		200
dialup modem		2		500
ISDN Line			2		150
T1/T3/OCR			2		80
10 ethernet			2		10
Wireless			2		600
